HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 428
By Capley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Trey Colvett, 2025 Top
Ten Senior of Mt. Pleasant High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Trey Colvett is one such exceptional student, who was recently named a
Top Ten Senior of the 2025 graduating class at Mt. Pleasant High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Mr. Colvett has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in his remarkable high school career, Trey Colvett has earned an exemplary
grade point average of 98.51 while participating in numerous extracurricular activities; and
WHEREAS, following his graduation, Mr. Colvett plans to attend the University of North
Alabama, where he intends to study sustainability; and
WHEREAS, apart from his scholastic endeavors, Mr. Colvett enjoys playing guitar and
fishing; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Colvett's display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well
for his future success; and
WHEREAS, his noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for his family,
his school, and his community; and
WHEREAS, Trey Colvett's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of the members of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
